# java 7
for most linux distros, just install the package `default-jdk`. however - 
programs like Android Studio will require java 8.

# java se development kit 8 (needed for Android Studio)
Follow these instructions:

	https://developer.android.com/studio/install.html

you'll now need to reconfigure your system to use java8 instead of java7.
follow these instructions after you've unzipped java8:

	https://www3.ntu.edu.sg/home/ehchua/programming/howto/Ubuntu_HowTo.html#jdk
